{"id": "html_001", "prompt": "Eli, build me a semantic blog post page. It should have a header with a site title, a main section containing an article, and a footer. The article should have an h1 title, some paragraph text, and an author byline.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["semantic-html", "css-layout"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has header", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "header", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has main", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "main", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has article inside main", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "main article", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has footer", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "footer", "expected": true}, {"description": "Article has h1", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "article h1", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_002", "prompt": "Can you create a simple contact form? It needs name, email, and message fields, plus a submit button. Make sure to use appropriate input types and a textarea for the message.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["form-components"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has form", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "form", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has email input", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input[type='email']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has text input", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input[type='text'], input:not([type])", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has textarea", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "textarea", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has submit button", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "button[type='submit'], input[type='submit'], button", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_003", "prompt": "Please make a responsive pricing table with 3 tiers: Basic, Pro, and Enterprise. Put them in a CSS flexbox or grid layout so they sit side-by-side on desktop.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["css-layout", "responsive"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has exactly 3 pricing tiers", "check_type": "element_count", "selector": ".card, .tier, .pricing-tier, div > div", "expected": 3}, {"description": "Check for basic text", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.body.textContent.toLowerCase().includes('basic')", "expected": true}, {"description": "Check for pro text", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.body.textContent.toLowerCase().includes('pro')", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_004", "prompt": "I need a navigation bar. It should have a nav element, a logo element on the left, and an unordered list of links (Home, About, Contact) on the right.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["semantic-html", "css-layout"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has nav element", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "nav", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has unordered list in nav", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "nav ul", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has at least 3 list items", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('nav ul li').length >= 3", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has at least 3 links", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('nav ul li a').length >= 3", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_005", "prompt": "Build a user profile card. It needs an image for the avatar, an h2 for the user's name, and a p tag for a short bio.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["css-layout"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has profile image", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "img", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has h2 for name", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "h2", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has bio paragraph", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "p", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_006", "prompt": "Create a standard login form. Include an email input, a password input, a 'remember me' checkbox, and a login button.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["form-components"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has form", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "form", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has password input", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input[type='password']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has checkbox", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input[type='checkbox']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has submit element", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "button, input[type='submit']", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_007", "prompt": "I need a simple 404 error page. It should have a large '404' heading, a message saying 'Page Not Found', and a link to go back to the homepage.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["semantic-html"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Heading has 404", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('h1, h2')).some(h => h.textContent.includes('404'))", "expected": true}, {"description": "Message includes not found", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.body.textContent.toLowerCase().includes('not found')", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has link", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "a", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_008", "prompt": "Create a responsive image gallery using CSS grid. Include at least 4 image tags placeholder sources inside a grid container.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["css-layout", "responsive"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has images", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('img').length >= 4", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_009", "prompt": "Write a basic FAQ list using the native HTML details and summary elements. Provide at least 3 questions and answers.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["semantic-html"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has details elements", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('details').length >= 3", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has summary elements", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('summary').length >= 3", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_010", "prompt": "Build a footer section containing copyright text (using the \u00a9 symbol) and an unordered list of social media links.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "easy", "tags": ["semantic-html"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has footer", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "footer", "expected": true}, {"description": "Footer has unordered list", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "footer ul", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has copyright symbol", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelector('footer').textContent.includes('\u00a9') || document.querySelector('footer').textContent.toLowerCase().includes('copyright')", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_011", "prompt": "Create an interactive counter component using JS. It needs a display showing the number '0', an 'Increment' button, and a 'Decrement' button.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["state-management", "event-handling"], "validation_type": "interaction", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has increment button", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "button", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has text '0' initially", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.body.textContent.includes('0')", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_012", "prompt": "Build a tabbed interface. There should be a row of 3 tab buttons and a content area below it. Clicking a tab should change the text in the content area to match that tab's content.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["interactive-widgets", "state-management"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has tab buttons", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('button, .tab').length >= 3", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_013", "prompt": "Create an accordion component using JavaScript (don't just use details/summary). There should be multiple sections with headers. Clicking a header expands its content and collapses others.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["interactive-widgets", "event-handling", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Does not use native details tag", "check_type": "element_count", "selector": "details", "expected": 0}, {"description": "Has interactive headers", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-header, button').length >= 2", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_014", "prompt": "Implement a modal dialog. There should be a button to 'Open Modal'. When clicked, a modal overlay appears containing some text and a 'Close' button.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["interactive-widgets", "event-handling"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has open button", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).some(b => b.textContent.toLowerCase().includes('open'))", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_015", "prompt": "Make a dark mode toggle. Add a button that, when clicked, toggles a 'dark' class on the document body to switch the background to a dark color and text to a light color.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["event-handling", "dom-manipulation", "state-management"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has toggle button", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "button", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_016", "prompt": "Create a form with custom client-side JavaScript validation. It should have an email field and a submit button. If the email doesn't contain an '@', prevent submission and show an error message element on the page.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["form-validation", "event-handling"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has form", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "form", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has email input", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_017", "prompt": "Build a character counter for a textarea. Below the textarea, display text like '0/200 characters'. As the user types, update the count dynamically.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["event-handling", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has textarea", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "textarea", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has counter display", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.body.textContent.includes('200')", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_018", "prompt": "Create a simple to-do list application. Include a text input and an 'Add' button. New items should appear in a list below, each with a 'Delete' button to remove it.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["dom-manipulation", "state-management"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has input field", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input[type='text']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has add button", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "button", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has list container", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "ul, ol", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_019", "prompt": "Implement a custom dropdown menu. There should be a button that says 'Options'. Clicking it reveals a list of choices below. Provide at least 3 choices.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["interactive-widgets", "event-handling"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has toggle button", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).some(b => b.textContent.toLowerCase().includes('option'))", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_020", "prompt": "Build a filterable list of items. Display an unordered list of fruits (e.g., Apple, Banana, Orange). Above it, add a search input. Typing in the input should hide list items that don't match the search text.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["dom-manipulation", "event-handling"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has search input", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input[type='text'], input[type='search']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has fruit list", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "ul", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has fruits", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('li').length >= 3", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_021", "prompt": "Create a custom tooltip component. When a user hovers over a specific span of text or an icon, a small tooltip bubble containing extra info should appear near it.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["interactive-widgets", "css-layout"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Tooltip container exists", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": ".tooltip, [data-tooltip]", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_022", "prompt": "Build an image carousel using JavaScript. Have a main image display area, and 'Next' and 'Previous' buttons to cycle through an array of image URLs.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "medium", "tags": ["interactive-widgets", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has main image", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "img", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has prev/next buttons", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('button').length >= 2", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_023", "prompt": "Build a multi-step wizard form. Step 1 asks for personal info (name, email), Step 2 for address, Step 3 is a review pane. Include 'Next' and 'Back' buttons to navigate between the steps.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "hard", "tags": ["state-management", "form-components", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has next/back buttons", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('button').length >= 2", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has form", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "form", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_024", "prompt": "Create a responsive data table. Include column headers for 'Name', 'Age', and 'Role'. Clicking on a column header should sort the table rows based on that column's data.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "hard", "tags": ["dom-manipulation", "event-handling", "responsive"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has table", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "table", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has headers", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "th", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has data rows", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('tbody tr').length >= 1", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_025", "prompt": "Implement a fully accessible custom select dropdown (replacing the native <select>). It must support opening/closing via mouse click, and keyboard navigation (up/down arrows to change selection, enter to select, escape to close). Use appropriate ARIA roles like listbox and option.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "hard", "tags": ["accessibility", "interactive-widgets", "event-handling"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has listbox role", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "[role='listbox']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has option role", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "[role='option']", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_026", "prompt": "Build a shopping cart component. Display a list of items with their individual prices, a quantity input for each, and a 'Remove' button. Show a total price at the bottom that updates automatically when quantities change or items are removed.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "hard", "tags": ["state-management", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has quantity inputs", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input[type='number']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has total display", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.body.textContent.toLowerCase().includes('total')", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_027", "prompt": "Create a password strength meter. As the user types in a password input field, update a visual indicator (like a colored bar) and a text label indicating strength (Weak, Medium, Strong). Enforce rules like minimum length, numbers, and special characters.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "hard", "tags": ["form-validation", "event-handling", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has password input", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input[type='password']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has strength indicator text", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.body.textContent.toLowerCase().includes('weak')", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_028", "prompt": "Build a simple rich text editor using the contenteditable attribute. Include a toolbar with buttons for 'Bold', 'Italic', and 'Underline' that format the selected text within the editor div.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "hard", "tags": ["interactive-widgets", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has contenteditable div", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "[contenteditable='true']", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has toolbar buttons", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('button').length >= 3", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_029", "prompt": "Implement a Kanban board layout with 3 columns: 'To Do', 'In Progress', and 'Done'. Add a form at the top to create a new task card, which should appear in the 'To Do' column initially. Include a button on each card to move it to the next column.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "hard", "tags": ["css-layout", "state-management", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has 3 columns", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('.column, section').length >= 3", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has input for new task", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "input", "expected": true}, {"description": "Has add button", "check_type": "element_exists", "selector": "button", "expected": true}]}
{"id": "html_030", "prompt": "Create an interactive star rating component. It should display 5 empty stars. Hovering over a star should fill it and all preceding stars. Clicking a star should lock in that rating value.", "language": "html", "difficulty": "hard", "tags": ["interactive-widgets", "event-handling", "dom-manipulation"], "validation_type": "dom_structure", "validation_checks": [{"description": "Has 5 stars", "check_type": "js_eval", "expression": "document.querySelectorAll('.star, svg, i, span').length >= 5", "expected": true}]}
